comment.text: This translation key is used to display a label indicating readiness to interact with a form. It appears as a button in a file editing interface and serves as a placeholder for the actual file name or content when it's not yet filled out.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "جاهز للتعبئة" (jahez lil ta'bi'ah) translates literally to 'ready for filling', it's not the most natural or common way to say "Ready to fill out" in Saudi Arabic. A more suitable translation would convey readiness for completion or completion of a form.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: جاهز للتعمير (jahez lil ta'mir) - meaning 'ready for completion' or 'جاهز للإكمال (jahez lil ikmal) - meaning 'ready for completion'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Doldurmağa hazırdır" is grammatically correct but doesn't perfectly capture the meaning of "Ready to fill out." It translates more literally to "Is ready to be filled."  A more natural and accurate translation would be closer to "Doldurulmağa hazırdır" or "Boşalmağa hazırdır".

The translation '今すぐ記入できる' (imasugu ki-nyuu dekiru) while generally meaning 'ready to fill out' or 'able to fill out now', is slightly more literal. A more natural and equivalent translation would be something like '記入可能です' (ki-nyuu kanou desu) or '記入できます' (ki-nyuu dekimasu). '今すぐ' (imasugu) - 'right now' adds a level of immediacy that might not be intended.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: 記入可能です (ki-nyuu kanou desu) or 記入できます (ki-nyuu dekimasu)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "작성 준비 완료" is understandable, it's a somewhat literal and formal translation. "Ready to fill out" implies a state of being prepared, which could be better conveyed with a more natural phrasing.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider alternatives like "작성 가능" (ready for writing) or "작성할 준비 됐어요" (I'm ready to fill it out). The best option depends on the context.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao translation "ພ້ອມແລ້ວທີ່ຈະຕື່ມຂໍ້ມູນເຂົ້າໄປ" is a literal translation and sounds overly formal and verbose for the simple English phrase "Ready to fill out". It's technically correct, but not natural.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more concise and natural translation like "ກຽມຕື່ມຂໍ້ມູນ" (Kieem toem khomun) or "ສາມາດຕື່ມຂໍ້ມູນໄດ້" (Samat toem khomun dai).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'කළු කිරීම සඳහා සුදානම්' literally translates to 'Ready for blackening/shading'. It doesn't accurately convey the meaning of 'Ready to fill out'. The intended meaning is likely 'Ready to be filled' or 'Fillable'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: සුදු කිරීම සඳහා සුදානම් (Ready to be filled)

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Спремни за попуњавање" is understandable, a more natural and common translation of "Ready to fill out" in Serbian (Cyrillic) would be "Готови за попуњавање". "Спремни" implies readiness in a more general sense, while "готови" specifically implies completion or preparedness for a task.
